==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sway bar
<hw>Sway bar</hw>. <fld>(Vehicles)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A bar
attached to the hounds, in the rear of the front axle, so as to slide on
the reach as the axle is swung in turning the vehicle.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Either of the two bars used on coupling the front and
rear sleds of a logging sled; also, the bar used to couple two logging
cars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sway-bracing</ent>⟦br⟧
